  "body": "\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nTG version: f20c08d18b477f10fbbaf49ac6dea52722f7ec4a\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu Server 20.04\r\nCommit hash : f20c08d18b477f10fbbaf49ac6dea52722f7ec4a\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI upgraded from 1828bb32faff1778e14e48703307cef9f43aefea to f20c08d18b477f10fbbaf49ac6dea52722f7ec4a on the master branch, using the same database.  \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThings seemed to work fine for a few days until today, where I am stuck with the following error:\r\n```\r\nSynchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"2/14 BlockHashes: put: k=dede8b9166645c34c82c9fbab1516c2eb8d24ef880f1360760963a677569e1ab, mdb_cursor_put: MDB_CORRUPTED: Located page was wrong type\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSync on the above mentioned commit hash, then after a full sync upgrade to the latter commit hash and wait.\r\n",
