    "body": "@ChosunOne it’s true. We are planing to switch TurboGeth from LMDB to MDBX. Partially because  we have facing db corruptions (in very rare cases), and because lmdb has no tool to detect corruptions or to check db. \r\n\r\nI think now it’s safe for you to switch to mdbx (we will make it default in near future). You can do it by: remove existing datadir, add flag —database=mdbx when run TurboGeth. \r\n\r\n Thank you for understanding. We can investigate problem by getting your db file, but it will take long time.",
